---
const questions = [
  {
    q: "Where are my codes stored?",
    a: "On your device, and only your device. They never leave your phone unless you choose to back them up.\n\nUnder the hood: codes are stored in the iOS Keychain, hardware-encrypted by the Secure Enclave. Account metadata like names and issuers lives in local storage. Nothing touches a server.",
  },
  {
    q: "Can I lock the app?",
    a: "Yes. Sesame supports Face ID, Touch ID, and device passcode. You can set it to lock as soon as you leave the app, or after a delay.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I lose my phone?",
    a: "If you\u2019ve enabled backups, you can restore everything to a new device. Sesame backs up to iCloud Drive or as a file you can store wherever you like, like an external drive or a cloud storage folder.",
  },
  {
    q: "How safe are my backups?",
    a: "Backups are encrypted with a password you choose before anything leaves your device. Without the password, the file is completely unreadable.\n\nFor the spec hunters: AES-256-GCM with Argon2id key derivation (3 iterations, 64 MB memory, 4 lanes). Your backup password is stored in the iOS Keychain and never leaves your device.",
  },
  {
    q: "What about iCloud backups?",
    a: "Everything is encrypted on your device before it reaches iCloud. What\u2019s stored on iCloud Drive is already unreadable without your password, with iCloud\u2019s own encryption on top.\n\nHeads up: if you use Sesame for your iCloud account\u2019s 2FA, make sure you have recovery codes saved somewhere safe. Without them, losing access to Sesame means losing access to iCloud.",
  },
  {
    q: "How does AutoFill work?",
    a: "Turn it on in Sesame settings and iOS will offer to fill in codes when you\u2019re logging into a website or app. You don\u2019t need to open Sesame.\n\nSesame registers your accounts with the iOS credential system, so codes appear inline wherever iOS supports AutoFill.",
  },
  {
    q: "What can Siri do?",
    a: "Ask Siri for a code by account name and it copies straight to your clipboard. You also get Spotlight search for your accounts and Shortcuts actions for automations.",
  },
];
---

<section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-xl">
    <div class="divide-y divide-seed/10">
      {
        questions.map((item) => (
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between py-5 text-lg font-semibold [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
              {item.q}
              <svg
                class="ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.5"
              >
                <line x1="10" y1="4" x2="10" y2="16" />
                <line x1="4" y1="10" x2="16" y2="10" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            {item.a.split("\n\n").map((line, i) => {
              const isLast = i === item.a.split("\n\n").length - 1;
              return (
                <p class={`${isLast ? "pb-5" : "pb-2"} text-base`}>
                  {line}
                  {!isLast && <br />}
                </p>
              );
            })}
          </details>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
